<task id="WKSP-044" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire wizard save flow to BFF API endpoints</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, code-page, bff-api</tags>
    <estimated-effort>5h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>021, 043</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Wire the Layout Wizard's save flow to the BFF API, handling create, edit, and Save As modes with proper error handling and dialog result communication.</goal>
    <context>
      The Layout Wizard operates in three modes:
      - Create: POST /api/workspace/layouts — new user workspace from scratch
      - Edit: PUT /api/workspace/layouts/{id} — update existing user workspace
      - Save As: POST /api/workspace/layouts — new workspace pre-filled from a system workspace

      The wizard collects templateId, slotAssignments (sectionId -> slot mapping), workspace name,
      and isDefault flag from the 3 wizard steps. This must be transformed into the API request
      body format (sprk_name, sprk_templateid, sprk_sectionsjson, sprk_isdefault).

      On success, the wizard dialog closes and returns the saved layout ID to the parent window
      via the navigateTo promise result. On failure, errors are displayed inline (e.g., max 10
      layouts reached, validation errors).
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Create mode MUST use POST /api/workspace/layouts
      - Edit mode MUST use PUT /api/workspace/layouts/{id}
      - Save As mode MUST use POST (creates new) with name pre-filled as "{name} (copy)"
      - MUST transform wizard state into correct API request body format
      - MUST handle error responses: max 10 layouts (409), validation errors (400)
      - MUST display errors inline using Fluent MessageBar component
      - On success, MUST close dialog and return result to parent via navigateTo promise
      - MUST show a saving/spinner state on the Save button during API call
      - MUST use /api prefix for all BFF API URLs per existing convention
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-026-full-page-custom-page-standard.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/src/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Create a buildLayoutPayload utility that transforms wizard state (templateId, slotAssignments, name, isDefault) into the API request body format with sprk_name, sprk_templateid, sprk_sectionsjson (serialized JSON), and sprk_isdefault.</step>
    <step id="2">Create a saveLayout async function that determines the HTTP method and URL based on wizard mode: POST for create/saveAs, PUT for edit. Include /api prefix on all URLs.</step>
    <step id="3">Wire the save function to the WizardDialog's final step "Save" button. Add loading state: disable the button and show Spinner while the API call is in flight.</step>
    <step id="4">Handle success response: extract the saved layout ID from the response, close the wizard dialog using Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo's close/result mechanism to pass the layout ID back to the parent window.</step>
    <step id="5">Handle error responses: parse error body, display specific messages using Fluent MessageBar — "Maximum 10 workspaces reached" for 409, field-level validation messages for 400, generic "Save failed" for other errors.</step>
    <step id="6">Handle Save As mode specifically: when mode is "saveAs", pre-fill the name as "{originalName} (copy)" in Step 3, and always use POST (never PUT) regardless of having an original layoutId.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Create mode successfully POSTs to /api/workspace/layouts and closes dialog on success</criterion>
    <criterion>Edit mode successfully PUTs to /api/workspace/layouts/{id} and closes dialog on success</criterion>
    <criterion>Save As mode POSTs a new layout with pre-filled name "{name} (copy)"</criterion>
    <criterion>Error responses display inline MessageBar with appropriate error messages</criterion>
    <criterion>Save button shows spinner during API call and is disabled to prevent double-submit</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
